= Soviet Elections 1929

The 1929 Soviet elections are the fiercest ones since the founding of the USSR. Ethnic tensions, anti-communist electoral campaigning and complaints about party privilege made this election heated. Opposition forces from the Orthodox Church and Left opposition would make their debut and many independents would be run. However our experts predict that these opposition forces will be unable to make a breakthrough on the ballot, however if we strategically support some canidates, we could make the Soviet Union friendlier to us.


- @meddle_in_elections: We strategically support friendly canidates.
- @let_the_ballot_cook: It's their democracy, not ours.

@meddle_in_elections
